[The reference for the article cited in items [1] and [2] above is:
Greninger AL, Naccache SN, Messacar K, et al: A novel outbreak enterovirus D68 strain associated with acute flaccid myelitis cases in the USA (2012-14): a retrospective cohort study. Lancet Infect Dis. Online First, 2015; abstract available at http://www.thelancet.com/journals/laninf/article/PIIS1473-3099(15)70093-9/abstract.

The analysis continues and the occurrence of enterovirus D68 continues to be associated with the occurrence of muscle weakness and paralysis in a small number of children. The majority of the cases have occurred in the United States and no other enterovirus has been implicated. Furthermore a specific strain of EV68, strain B1, appears to be the only strain of EV68 associated with neurological effects. - Mod.CP]
